-# VoxelCraft Survival V2
+# VoxelCraft Survival V3
 
 A native voxel survival sandbox built with Godot 4.6 and the Voxel Tools 1.6 C++ module. V2 replaces the original debug-like prototype with a proper procedural world, surface-safe spawning, survival HUD, mining feedback, item pickups, crafting, day/night, hostile mobs, sound, and an original pixel-art texture atlas.
 
@@ -22,3 +22,16 @@
 GitHub Actions uses the pinned Voxel Tools custom Godot build, runs import checks, boots the menu, creates a real test world, waits for terrain around spawn to mesh, and only then exports the Windows executable.
 
 This is an original clean-room project. It aims for the familiar feel of a block survival sandbox without redistributing Minecraft code, textures, sounds, names, or other Mojang assets.
+
+
+## V3 validation gate
+
+The Windows build is published only after the custom Godot/Voxel Tools editor:
+
+- imports every resource without script errors,
+- boots the main menu and reaches `VOXELCRAFT_BOOT_OK`,
+- generates a fresh deterministic world and waits for spawn chunks,
+- verifies a solid non-water spawn floor and clear head space, and
+- reaches `VOXELCRAFT_WORLD_SMOKE_OK` before export.
+
+V3 uses a separate world/save namespace so prototype saves cannot corrupt new worlds.
